        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### Overview\n\nThe SRD-46 database holds **38 VLM (value-measurement) records** for the Cd²⁺–Cl⁻ system (metal_26 / ligand_5781). These 38 records all resolve to a **single recommended network** of four stepwise complexes, and the citation evidence shows they all trace back to **one primary experimental source** — the landmark 1947 paper by Schwarzenbach & Ackermann — which has been cited and re-evaluated across **38 successive NIST/IUPAC critical compilation volumes** (shortcut codes 41Sc through 83Sc). The SRD-46 architecture records each compilation edition as a separate citation entry, which is why the VLM count is 38 rather than 38 independent experimental studies.",
